webpackJsonp([0x704470c6aa8e],{8087:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{post:{html:'<p>Nest week we start a new remodelling project... the satellite in Marktkauf Center. The design hasn\'t changed since it opened nearly 8 years ago:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/51035717986@N01/3444266848" title="View \'Presentation existing\' on Flickr.com"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3566/3444266848_102e3cdeab.jpg" alt="Presentation existing" border="0" width="500" height="354" /></a></p>\n<p>The designers for McDonald\'s Europe in Paris have a new series of designs for satellites, and they imagine that our restaurant could look like this:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/51035717986@N01/3443451907" title="View \'Presentation project\' on Flickr.com"><img src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3298/3443451907_46f6006f18.jpg" alt="Presentation project" border="0" width="500" height="354" /></a></p>\n<p>The transformation will take just 3 days, and the restaurant will remain open throughout construction. The French models photoshopped into the proposed design are not included. :-)</p>\n<p>Note that the central M logo is placed on a green background instead of the traditional red. It\' part of a new exterior design scheme that\'s being implemented in Europe. It\'s a bit hard to get used to after 50 years of red.</p>',fields:{title:"Stripes from Paris",date:"15 Apr 2009",url:"https://papascott.de/2009-04-15-stripes-from-paris/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2009-04-15-stripes-from-paris/",prev:{fields:{title:"Yesterday's News",date:"23 Mar 2009",slug:"/2009-03-23-yesterdays-news/"}},next:{fields:{title:"Whiney Expat Bloggers Meetup 2009",date:"28 Apr 2009",slug:"/2009-04-28-whiney-expat-bloggers-meetup-2009/"}}}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---2009-04-15-stripes-from-paris-2dac2416354ef2b9f3e0.js.map